sence my last of 3 cur 5 posts come by them yours of 15:18:22
& 29 past first with a remise of 4 Â£200:- on Piwoelaert which
is well seenge exs comes so low remitt no more, by the second I have
the bill on S stephen Ewans with protes for charges where of you
have credit 3 p, I feared itt would comeso & therefore have no pard
the drawer afarting. I have the patt of 3 packes of 1 pas clothes amonge
them severall which I suppose bought for peirle cullours, which
will not do, itt is a miserable thing: I blamed you last yeare for buying
N 360 in N53 & told you I would not accept there of att itt is no
bodde will loose upon that cullour & will never sell N 366 in N55
& N375 & 382 in N56, & N388 in N57 are the vere same for
donles apeirle cullour be upon the blew & to the patt. N3 of 20 Janu
I can not sell them & I have yett 6 a d such light cullours which will
not sell for want they be not upon the blew & if you please to examen
my patt of 20 past with all these not one comes by all the grayes so
N2 & 5 of 16 xber & to N4 of 20 past are most wanting & them
I want first & above all some patt loock vere treadbare & principally
4 in N 57 pray S send mee no clothes what are sappy or thread bare
& above all no light cullours butt that they be as I order for tis not
to be expressed what paines wee have in selling & for perle cullours you
have now so often send mee miserable cullours they I all a long told
you I would have non exceptas I send my patt I hope a pack
of northrens & the bayes shall comes with this convoy for
Rott & you could doe mee aservice to send mee a pack of
white kersies of 30 yearde of 40 a 50 p of the best sort if
you have anney for yours actt or to spare att hull with sayd
convoij pray do itt the second pack of northrens I exspect
& frost convoij for ostend as also the rest of my orders com
=pleated & pack whites EE yeallow marckes if reasouable to your
content, I might wish wee might have soone convoj of
one for Rott send N57 that way & advise wheat passxs frest

5 post beenge come att home finde yours of 18 past for the futture
in the invoyces from the nord doe as best is to be don I knom yours sin-
ceritye that I shall satisfie my self there with, & if itt bee more or less you
can rectifie int in the acct cur my kersies & baeys arestill att Amstt & I
wish I had soo kersies more there if you have anney att hull or abrard
the vessels for Rott I am continded for 50 a 60 p if you can serve
mee there in if not itt shall be for next opportunitie as them
Ishall order the acct of tykes is vere pitefull & loosinge yett to
content because I am sure of your endeavour, you are mistaken in the
charges if costoite & beet 18:19:5 a great article you mis last 10 p
then insteed off 128:5:6 the proceed shall bee onley Â£128:15:6
butt I hope those charges are oulef 18:9:3 as you order shall directivild
when you meet, the E yeallow marcks to content you may buy them
the patt of mode culd are not particular I hope with the fouwinge
wheather marketts will be better stoled, of which pray your opinion
to take my measures, a to m batkin I know no better butt he
be well with his wises parents he vs avere civil & actire man had
he butt monney enough all thingh would be well, butt of him self
he hath vere little of his wise is to have itt all & which will be
considerable, butt that can not help him new, so could advise you
to g0 on moderateley, butt what needs that sence notingh is to be
done sence monney with you & when he remitt you or you draw
on him is a creditt of small time
